UPDATE Config SET Value="<h3> Brain Development in Autism: Infant Siblings</h3>\n<p>This study is a collaborative effort by investigators at four clinical sites: University of North Carolina (UNC), University of Washington (UW), Washington University in St. Louis (WUSTL), and the Children\'s Hosptial in Philadelphia (CHOP); and one data coordinating center (DCC) at the Montreal Neurological Institute (MNI), to conduct a longitudinal MRI/DTI and behavioral study of infants at high risk for autism (i.e., siblings of autistic individuals) at 6, 12, 24 and 36 months of age.\n</p><p>\nThis website serves as the starting point for all project personnel. From this page, access to all web-related tools is available, inlcuding the IBIS database. Much of the contents of this website are restricted and require authentication to access various components. For account information please contact the DCC. For more information of each tool/webpage, please click on the appropriate link on the left menu.\n</p><p>\nFor details on the teleconference minutes and agendas, upcoming conferences, or any discussions about the various protocols (both behavioral or imaging), please access the Wiki or OWL (links on the left menu). To access the project personnel link, please use the wiki login information.\n</p>\n<h3>Useful Links </h3>\n<a href=\'https://pandora.ia.unc.edu/ace_wiki/\'>Wiki</a><br>\n<a href=\'http://ibis-network.org/\'>Main Recruitment Site</a><br>\n<a href=\'http://www.bic.mni.mcgill.ca/autism/mailing_lists.html\'>Mailing Lists</a><br>\n<a href=\'http://www.bic.mni.mcgill.ca/autism/Age_calc/age_calculator.html\'>Window Age Calculator</a><br>\n<a href=\'http://www.bic.mni.mcgill.ca/autism/faq.html\'>FAQ</a>\n" WHERE ConfigID=(SELECT ID FROM ConfigSettings WHERE Name="StudyDescription");
